isUnderground().Description: Returns true if the building is entirely underground.

getActiveLevelIndex().Description: Gets the index in the list returned by @B_com#google#android#gms#maps#model#IndoorBuilding#getLevels_E@ of the level that is currently active in this building (default if no active level was previously set).

getLevels().Description: Gets the levels in the building. While a level is usually enclosed by a single building, a level might be enclosed by several buildings (e.g., a carpark level might span multiple buildings). The levels are in 'display order' from top to bottom.

getDefaultLevelIndex().Description: Gets the index in the list returned by @B_com#google#android#gms#maps#model#IndoorBuilding#getLevels_E@ of the default level for this building.

ClassDesc: Represents a building. Two IndoorBuildings are .equal() if the physical building they represent is the same. However, if a building's structural model changes, e.g., due to an update to Google's building models, then an old IndoorBuilding object and a new IndoorBuilding object will be .equal(), but might have different contents.
